  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong><br />We are seeking a Technical Lead / Project Manager to lead the technical and product workstream of an initiative focused on resource utilisation and sustainability-linked solutions. The role will work closely with commercial, operations, and investment teams to shape, validate, and deliver scalable, deployable solutions.</p><p>You will be responsible for:</p><ul><li>Evaluating resource streams and associated processing or conversion pathways</li><li>Developing and testing technical concepts and pilots</li><li>Translating concepts and pilots into practical, deployable solutions</li><li>Supporting technical due diligence and investment decisions</li></ul><p>This is a full-time contract role (5–6 months) based in Singapore, with regular travel across Southeast Asia.<br /><br /></p><p>Required</p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Chemical, Process, Mechanical Engineering, Bioengineering, or a related field</li><li>5–8 years of experience in process engineering or industrial operations, including exposure to power systems, agri-processing, or manufacturing environments</li><li>Experience in biomass, biofuels, biogas, or waste-to-energy projects</li><li>Ability to translate technical concepts and pilot technologies into practical, scalable solutions</li><li>Strong analytical, problem-solving, and stakeholder communication skills</li></ul><h3>Preferred</h3><ul><li>Master’s or PhD in Chemical/Process Engineering, Bioengineering, or related fields</li><li>Experience with modular processing technologies (e.g. mobile equipment)</li><li>Familiarity with industrial energy users (e.g. cement, textile) and their fuel/boiler needs</li><li>Experience working in cross-functional teams with commercial, operations, and R&D stakeholders</li></ul>",
